      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:3:3:4",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) النِّسَاءُ أَرْبَعٌ جَامِعٌ مُجْمِعٌ وَ رَبِيعٌ مُرْبِعٌ وَ خَرْقَاءُ مُقْمِعٌ وَ غُلٌّ قَمِلٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Salma Bin Al Khattab, from Suleyman Bin Sama’at, from Al Haza’a, from his uncle Aasim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘The women are four (types) – An all inclusive goodness, and a child-bearing fountain, and a careless destructive one, and a feed for parasite’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "4. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Safmah ibn al-Khattab from Sulayman ibn Sama‘ah from al-Hadhdha’ from his uncle, ‘Asem who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that the Messenger of Allah, O Allah, grant compensation to Muhammad and his family worthy of their services to Your cause, has said, ’Women are of four kinds: Goodness in all respects, a child bearing fountain, a dimwitted destructive one and feed for parasites.”’ "
        ]
      }
